We had wanted to come here for a while. My Mama-in-law was in town and we thought it would be a great time. We were greeted warmly with friendly smiles as if we coming to your auntie's house to eat and she was happy to see you. It was about 2:00p and we were the only customers at the start but others entered shortly after us. The service was great and attentive.  My daughter and I split the  jibaritos lechon and bistec. She got french fries instead of rice. I was pleasantly surprised about how good the jibaritos were. The meat was super flavorful. The plantains were caramelized, crunchy on outside but tender on the inside. The fries and yucc mojo were perfectly cooked: good and crispy. The mojo had the perfect tang and garlic bite.  My mama-in-law had the Chuleta con arroz y frijoles negros. She liked the rice but likes her pork chops a little less done.  My hubby had ropa vieja con arroz con grandules which he said was "great and flavorful."  The cafe cubano and cafe de leche were  delicious!! Both Strong but smooth.  My hubby had to get a third cafe cubano!  All in all, everything was great and worth the wait. We are definitely coming back for the food and to try Fabi's cafe next time cause she said she can make an even better cup of coffee.

Once every two or three weeks I stop on my way home from work and grab take out dinner here. The folks that work here, host, cook, even the  owner, are as inviting and enjoyable to be around as their food is amazing and authentic to dine on. Absolutely the best in Chigago.
Looking for some authentic Cuban restaurant in Chicago this hidden gem won't disappoint you! Food was fantastic and the service was impressive.. can't wait to go back!

Went to lunch there today. It wasn't very busy but it took 25 minutes for two sandwiches and some rice. My sandwich was a little burnt, the ingredients weren't fresh, and I felt like I could have made it at home. My coworker said her sandwich was okay but she wouldn't get it again. The entrees looked good though. The atmosphere was hectic and one of staff's child was screaming for the majority of my wait. Would not return.
